Postman Collection Variables to Set
In your Postman collection, set these variables and update them as you create each record:
VariableDescription{{token}}Access token from login response{{classId}}_id from create class response{{teacherId}}_id from create teacher response{{studentId}}_id from create student response{{parentId}}_id from create parent response{{attendanceId}}_id from mark attendance response{{feeId}}_id from create fee response{{resultId}}_id from create result response{{timetableId}}_id from create timetable response{{warningId}}_id from create warning response

Correct Testing Order
1.  POST /users/register        → create admin
2.  POST /users/login           → get token → set {{token}}
3.  POST /teachers/             → create teacher → set {{teacherId}}
4.  POST /classes/              → create class (use teacherId) → set {{classId}}
5.  POST /students/             → create student (use classId) → set {{studentId}}
6.  POST /parents/              → create parent → set {{parentId}}
7.  POST /parents/link-student  → link parent to student
8.  POST /timetable/            → create schedule
9.  POST /attendance/           → mark attendance
10. POST /fees/                 → create fee record
11. POST /results/              → enter result
12. POST /warnings/             → issue warning